{"word":"ἐπιτυγχάνω","slug":"ἐπιτυγχάνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιτυγχάνω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-τεύξομαι</el>) (aor2 <el>ἐπέτῠχον</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>properly, <i>to hit the mark</i>: hence <i>to light</i> or <i>fall upon, meet with</i>, <p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ὁ ἐπιτυχών</el>, like <el>ὁ τυχών</el>, <i>the first person one meets, any one</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to attain to, reach, gain</i> one's end, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <i>to succeed in</i> doing, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> modi, <i>to be successful in</i> a thing, <el>μάχῃ</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to succeed, be successful</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><el>ἐπ. βιβλίῳ</el> <i>to read</i> it, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}